# =============================================================
#  tools/samples/ — local-only outputs
# =============================================================
# Two categories of output land here; both are blocked by the blanket
# rule below, with only README.md and .gitkeep allowed through:
#
#   1. Decoded copyrighted artifacts (tools/probe_*.py outputs — PNGs of
#      TGIFILE.ART entries, audio clips from Music.dat / Sfx.dat /
#      Voice.dat, raw palette dumps). Derived from Warner Bros. /
#      Hanna-Barbera material; never commit. See tools/samples/README.md
#      for the copyright posture.
#   2. Regenerable diagnostic outputs (asset-catalog.json,
#      unmatched-assets.txt, wp003-name-table.txt). Not copyrighted
#      derivatives, but reproducible from SHA-256-locked source binaries
#      via the tooling under tools/; committing them adds noise and
#      drifts from the canonical regeneration.
#
# The policy README stays in git so the discipline is visible.
tools/samples/*
!tools/samples/README.md
!tools/samples/.gitkeep

# Local copies of Scooby.exe and other game binaries pulled from mounted ISOs
# for analysis (rich_header.py, Ghidra, etc.). Copyrighted game binaries
# — never commit. The README documents the workflow.
tools/exes/*
!tools/exes/README.md
!tools/exes/.gitkeep

# Findings dirs that may contain partial extractions or disc listings
docs/findings/*
!docs/findings/README.md
!docs/findings/.gitkeep

# =============================================================
#  Original game data — safety net
# =============================================================
# Backstop against accidentally copying disc contents into the repo.
# Live discs / ISOs live at C:\pcloud\SCOOBY\ — outside this repo.
*.iso
Scooby.exe
Scooby.eng
TGIFILE.ART
Music.dat
Sfx.dat
Voice.dat
object.ini
BK.*
binkw32.dll

# =============================================================
#  Jekyll / GitHub Pages
# =============================================================
_site/
.jekyll-cache/
.jekyll-metadata
.sass-cache/
vendor/

# =============================================================
#  Python (tools/)
# =============================================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
venv/
env/
.python-version
*.egg-info/

# =============================================================
#  Ghidra projects — large, personal, hold proprietary analysis state
# =============================================================
ghidra/
*.gpr
*.rep/
*.lock

# =============================================================
#  OS / editor
# =============================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.bak
